ds on whether the Indonesian government and other pluralist forces are able to control the Islamists and provide political stability and economic development in the country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Apr 2019) 4aReligion, Politics & State. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2018z978311060677540uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/9789814818681423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814818681.jpg  a978-3-11-060677-5  ISEAS eBook Package 2018  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG